Reasoning: The paper focuses on the design and analysis of distributed algorithms in cognitive radio networks, which are a type of wireless network. This topic falls under the sub-category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency and reliability of wireless communication, which is related to Information Theory (cs.IT). The algorithms proposed in the paper also involve scheduling and coordination, which are topics in Distributed Computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the heterogeneous nature of cognitive radio networks, which can be related to Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the time complexity of the algorithms, which is a topic in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
